    T - the required type of class which implement WebElement. Instances of the defined type will be returned via findElement* and findElements*. Warning (!!!). Allowed types: WebElement TouchableElement RemoteWebElement MobileElement IOSElement

      • hideKeyboard

        public void hideKeyboard(String strategy,
                String keyName)
        Description copied from interface: IOSDeviceActionShortcuts
        Hides the keyboard if it is showing. Available strategies are PRESS_KEY and TAP_OUTSIDE. One taps outside the keyboard, the other presses a key of your choosing (probably the 'Done' key). Hiding the keyboard often depends on the way an app is implemented, no single strategy always works.
        Specified by:
        hideKeyboard in interface IOSDeviceActionShortcuts
        Parameters:
        strategy - HideKeyboardStrategy.
        keyName - a String, representing the text displayed on the button of the keyboard you want to press. For example: "Done".
        See Also:
        IOSDeviceActionShortcuts.hideKeyboard(String, String).

      • findElement

        public T findElement(org.openqa.selenium.By by)
        Description copied from interface: WebDriver
        Find the first WebElement using the given method. This method is affected by the 'implicit wait' times in force at the time of execution. The findElement(..) invocation will return a matching row, or try again repeatedly until the configured timeout is reached.

        findElement should not be used to look for non-present elements, use WebDriver.findElements(By) and assert zero length response instead.

        Specified by:
        findElement in interface MobileDriver<T extends WebElement>
        Specified by:

        Overrides:

        Parameters:

        Returns:
